{"id":92711,"title":"Atopic dermatitis: skin-directed management.","abstract":"Atopic dermatitis is a common inflammatory skin condition characterized by relapsing eczematous lesions in a typical distribution. It can be frustrating for pediatric patients, parents, and health care providers alike. The pediatrician will treat the majority of children with atopic dermatitis as many patients will not have access to a pediatric medical subspecialist, such as a pediatric dermatologist or pediatric allergist. This report provides up-to-date information regarding the disease and its impact, pathogenesis, treatment options, and potential complications. The goal of this report is to assist pediatricians with accurate and useful information that will improve the care of patients with atopic dermatitis. ","date":"2014-12-02","categories":"Skin and Connective Tissue Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25422009","annotations":[{"name":"Dermatology","weight":0.820237,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatology"},{"name":"Allergy","weight":0.812569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allergy"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.760342,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Inflammation","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inflammation"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Pathogenesis","weight":0.689375,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogenesis"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.682664,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.679861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.611976,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Therapy","